1. DEFINITIONS
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
"Software" or "Yggdrasil Engine" refers to all files, data,
formulas, models, documentation, JSON structures, systems,
architectures, pipelines, diagrams, theoretical or
procedural content contained in this repository, including
any proprietary formulas, mathematical innovations, cosmological
structures, rune pipelines, creature-generation logic, and all
other intellectual property disclosed herein.

"Personal Use" means use by an individual solely for:
• private experimentation,
• academic learning,
• hobby projects,
• non-commercial worldbuilding,
• non-commercial games or prototypes,
• non-monetized creative works.
Personal Use explicitly excludes any activities that generate
revenue, commercial value, or involve corporate/enterprise
environments, even if indirect.

"Commercial Use" means any use that directly or indirectly
generates revenue or commercial value, including but not limited to:
• commercial game development,
• commercial tools or plugins,
• paid educational products or courses,
• subscription-based platforms,
• monetized media or derivative works,
• corporate or enterprise use,
• any integration into products or services offered for sale,
lease, or subscription.

“Educational Use”
“Educational Use” means use of the Software by students, educators, academic researchers, or accredited educational institutions solely for non‑commercial teaching, learning, or research purposes, including:
• classroom instruction and demonstrations,  
• academic assignments, capstone projects, or coursework,  
• non‑commercial university or laboratory research,  
• thesis or dissertation work,  
• non‑profit educational analysis, review, or study of the Software.
Educational Use does not include:
• paid courses, paid workshops, or paid training programs,  
• use within for‑profit educational platforms or institutions,  
• corporate or enterprise training,  
• research performed under commercial contracts or grants,  
• any activity that generates revenue, tuition‑based profit, or commercial value.
---
“Independent Developer Use”
“Independent Developer Use” means use of the Software by a single individual game developer or sole proprietor who:
• develops games or interactive works independently (not as part of a company or studio), and  
• earns less than 1,000,000 USD in total gross revenue from all product sales in any calendar year.
Independent Developer Use is strictly non‑commercial beyond this revenue threshold and is subject to all other terms, restrictions, and obligations of this License. Any developer exceeding this threshold, operating as a multi‑person studio, or engaging in commercial distribution must obtain a separate commercial license.

"Creator" means Flynn, the original author and copyright holder.

"Contributions" means any code, documentation, or other materials
submitted by third parties via pull requests or other means.

